<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Myrthos on 05-05-2002 11:08 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL"> [QUOTE]Originally posted by Moriendor:
[i]1) Why does Grugar, the zombie, attack the orcs around Smiruk? Seems like a logical bug. If I am neutral towards them then Grugar should not attack them either.[/i][/QUOTE]
I disagree, Grugar has been told to defend you at all times and he can only do simple tasks. In the dungeon that means if it moves, kill it!
He doesn't know the orcs are neutral to you, so he starts attacking them. If this should be solved then it should be solved by allowing you to give a simple command like 'Attack' or 'Stand', but as you can not his behaviour towards the orcs seems correct to me.

 [QUOTE]Originally posted by Moriendor:
[i]2) It is at times difficult to tell whether a stairway in the dungeons leads up or down.[/i][/QUOTE]
Can't say I share that feeling. I had no troubles identifying them as far as I know. Is it maybe too dark?

 [QUOTE]Originally posted by Moriendor:
[i]12) In general, it would be great if you could move levers only once. I really hate it when I have no clue what the default position of a lever was and it makes it easier to determine whether you've already used a lever or not.[/i][/QUOTE]
I do not agree, you should remember to pull the lever only once.



